# MCP Tools: tavily

ALWAYS include `arguments` in CallMcpTool calls. NEVER send empty `{}`.

### tavily_research
Perform comprehensive research on a topic or question. Rate limit: 20 requests/minute.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| input | string | Yes | - | Comprehensive description of the research task |
| model | string | No | auto | Depth: mini, pro, auto |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "tavily", toolName: "tavily_research", arguments: { input: "Latest advancements in quantum computing 2026", model: "pro" } })

### tavily_map
Map a website's structure starting from a base URL.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| url | string | Yes | - | Root URL to begin mapping |
| max_depth | integer | No | 1 | Max depth to explore |
| max_breadth | integer | No | 20 | Max links to follow per page |
| limit | integer | No | 50 | Total links to process |
| instructions | string | No | "" | Natural language instructions for the crawler |
| select_paths | array | No | [] | Regex patterns to select URL paths |
| select_domains | array | No | [] | Regex patterns to restrict domains |
| allow_external | boolean | No | true | Whether to return external links |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "tavily", toolName: "tavily_map", arguments: { url: "https://example.com", max_depth: 2, limit: 100 } })

### tavily_crawl
Crawl a website starting from a URL and extract page content.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| url | string | Yes | - | Root URL to begin crawl |
| max_depth | integer | No | 1 | Max depth to explore |
| max_breadth | integer | No | 20 | Max links to follow per page |
| limit | integer | No | 50 | Total links to process |
| instructions | string | No | "" | Natural language instructions |
| select_paths | array | No | [] | Regex patterns to select URL paths |
| select_domains | array | No | [] | Regex patterns to restrict domains |
| allow_external | boolean | No | true | Whether to return external links |
| extract_depth | string | No | basic | basic or advanced |
| format | string | No | markdown | markdown or text |
| include_favicon | boolean | No | false | Include favicon URL per result |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "tavily", toolName: "tavily_crawl", arguments: { url: "https://example.com/docs", extract_depth: "advanced", format: "markdown" } })

### tavily_extract
Extract content from URLs in markdown or text format.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| urls | array | Yes | - | List of URLs to extract |
| extract_depth | string | No | basic | basic or advanced |
| include_images | boolean | No | false | Include images from pages |
| format | string | No | markdown | markdown or text |
| include_favicon | boolean | No | false | Include favicon URLs |
| query | string | No | "" | Query to rerank content chunks |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "tavily", toolName: "tavily_extract", arguments: { urls: ["https://example.com/article"], extract_depth: "advanced" } })

### tavily_search
Search the web for current information.

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
|-------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
| query | string | Yes | - | Search query |
| max_results | integer | No | 5 | Maximum results to return |
| search_depth | string | No | basic | basic, advanced, fast, ultra-fast |
| topic | string | No | general | Always general |
| time_range | string\|null | No | null | day, week, month, year |
| include_images | boolean | No | false | Include query-related images |
| include_image_descriptions | boolean | No | false | Include images with descriptions |
| include_raw_content | boolean | No | false | Include cleaned HTML per result |
| include_domains | array | No | [] | Domains to specifically include |
| exclude_domains | array | No | [] | Domains to specifically exclude |
| country | string | No | "" | Full country name to boost results |
| include_favicon | boolean | No | false | Include favicon URL per result |
| start_date | string | No | "" | YYYY-MM-DD |
| end_date | string | No | "" | YYYY-MM-DD |
| exact_match | boolean\|null | No | null | Only return exact phrase matches |

Example:
CallMcpTool({ server: "tavily", toolName: "tavily_search", arguments: { query: "latest AI news", max_results: 10, search_depth: "advanced" } })
